 ring with a width of\n75+/-3 AU centered at 190+/-3 AU. The influence of a companion and protoplanet\non the dust evolution is investigated. The companion at 10 AU facilitates the\naccumulation of mm-sized grains within a compact ring, ~ 20 - 30 AU, by ~ 10\nMyr. The injection of a protoplanet at 1 Myr hastens the ring formation (~ 1.2\nMyr) and also triggers the development of an outer ring (~ 100 - 200 AU). These\nobservations provide additional evidence for the presence of a close-in\ncompanion and hint at dynamical clearing by a protoplanet in the outer disk.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 May 2014 11:05:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 10 Jul 2014 14:24:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-19"}
